@node "History"

1.0   - First release

1.1   - Bugfix: QWKDoor didn't accept reply packets called .RE2, .RE2 etc

      - Bugfix: QWKDoor 1.0 refused to accept reply packets if your BBSID
        was 8 chars long.

      - QWKDoor now also intercepts control messages to QWK, UQWK and
        JCQWK and not only to QWKDOOR. But all control messages generated
        by offline-readers really should be addressed to QWKDOOR since
        that is what QWKDoor tells the reader to use in the DOOR.ID file...

      - QWKDoor now has a third command for offline-configuration: RESET.
        "RESET xxx" on the subject line changes the number of unread
        messages in the area the message was writted in.

      - The user can now select between "Strict QWK" and "Extended QWK".
        In "Extended QWK", no case-conversion at all is done on the
        headers and area names may be up to 40 characters long and not
        only 13. The next time a user enters the door, he will be asked
        what type of QWK he wants to use.

        WARNING: The long area names may cause some readers to crash.

      - An asterisk ("*") is now also shown before the tagged areas
        in thge "Edit Unread" part.

      - The part about offline-configuration has been improved in
        QWK_User.doc.

      - There were some references to an ANSI switch in the manual. I
        originally planned to have optional colourful ANSI menus in QWKDoor,
        but I didn't manage to make any good-looking ANSI screens. I dropped
        that feature, but forgot to remove it from the manual.

        If you think you can make nice ANSI-screens, please do so and send
        them to me. Please don't use any of the IBMPC graphics characters.

      - In the previous versions, "%%" in archiver and transfer strings
        wasn't replaced with a single "%" character.

        YOU MAY HAVE TO CHANGE YOUR SCRIPTS/SETTINGS!

      - New switch: NOASK. QWKDoor will never stop the uploading or
        or downloading of messages to ask the user for something.

      - New switch: NOPROGRESS. QWKDoor will no longer display the
        %-indicator when downloading messages.

@endnode

