@node "Glossary"

 @{".newsrc    " link g_newsrc}
 @{"QWK        " link g_qwk}
 @{"QWK Door   " link g_door}
 @{"QWK Reader " link g_reader}

@endnode

@node g_newsrc ".newsrc"

This file is used by some newsreaders to store what areas are tagged and
what messages have been read. It might look like this:

comp.sys.amiga.datacomm: 1-100 105
alt.jokes.tastless! 1-10000

Areas with ":" are tagged and areas with "!" are untagged.
@endnode

@node g_qwk "QWK"

QWK is a format for downloading messages so that you can read them at home
later without having to worry about large phonebills. QWK is the most common
format today and there are many readers. There is also another format called
BlueWave, but it isn't as common as QWK yet. Perhaps BlueWave will be
supported in future versions of QWKDoor.
@endnode

@node g_door "QWK Door"

The QWK Door is the program used on the BBS to pack the messages and send
them to the user.
@endnode

@node g_reader "QWK Reader"
The QWK Reader is the program that the user uses to read the downloaded
messages and to write replies.

Examples: AmiQWK (Amiga), Q-Blue (Amiga), BlueWave (MS-DOS)

(Don't get confused by BlueWave, the BlueWave _reader_ can read both
BlueWave and QWK bundles)
@endnode


